  "instructions": [
    "Slice the eggplant into 1-inch cubes.",
    "Heat coconut oil in a skillet over medium heat and add the eggplant, cooking until golden and softened, about 8 minutes.",
    "Stir in minced garlic, ginger, and sliced chili; cook for 2 minutes.",
    "Add tamari, fish sauce, lime juice, and sugar; stir to coat and simmer for 3 minutes until the sauce thickens.",
    "Remove the skillet from the heat and whisk in the egg until the mixture becomes silky and well incorporated.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a bowl and sprinkle with chopped cilantro and toasted sesame seeds.",
    "Serve immediately with cauliflower rice or a side of low-carb greens."
